properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 2:14PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS EVENING AND OVERNIGHT...

.Snow will arrive early this evening, bringing total snowfall
accumulations of 1 to 4 inches southeast of a line from
Washington Island to Oshkosh. The heaviest snowfall is expected in
Manitowoc County. Along with the snowfall, blowing and drifting
snow is likely, especially along lakeshore counties due to north
to northeast winds gusting up to 40 mph. Travel conditions will be
significantly impacted along the lakeshore.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of up to two
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph.

* WHERE...Kewaunee County.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing and
drifting snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds
could bring down tree branches, resulting in localized power
outages.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
